#: src/1535-stable-overflow-checks.md:9
msgid "Stabilize the `-C overflow-checks` command line argument."
msgstr ""

#: src/1535-stable-overflow-checks.md:11
msgid "Motivation"
msgstr "動機"

#: src/1535-stable-overflow-checks.md:14
msgid ""
"This is an easy way to turn on overflow checks in release builds without "
"otherwise turning on debug assertions, via the `-C debug-assertions` flag. "
"In stable Rust today you can't get one without the other."
msgstr ""

#: src/1535-stable-overflow-checks.md:19
msgid ""
"Users can use the `-C overflow-checks` flag from their Cargo config to turn "
"on overflow checks for an entire application."
msgstr ""

#: src/1535-stable-overflow-checks.md:22
msgid ""
"This flag, which accepts values of 'yes'/'no', 'on'/'off', is being renamed "
"from `force-overflow-checks` because the `force` doesn't add anything that "
"the 'yes'/'no'"
msgstr ""

#: src/1535-stable-overflow-checks.md:26
msgid "Detailed design"
msgstr "詳細設計"

#: src/1535-stable-overflow-checks.md:29
msgid ""
"This is a stabilization RFC. The only steps will be to move `force-overflow-"
"checks` from `-Z` to `-C`, renaming it to `overflow-checks`, and making it "
"stable."
msgstr ""

#: src/1535-stable-overflow-checks.md:33
msgid "Drawbacks"
msgstr ""

#: src/1535-stable-overflow-checks.md:36
msgid "It's another rather ad-hoc flag for modifying code generation."
msgstr ""

#: src/1535-stable-overflow-checks.md:38
msgid ""
"Like other such flags, this applies to the entire code unit, regardless of "
"monomorphizations. This means that code generation for a single function can "
"be different based on which code unit it's instantiated in."
msgstr ""

#: src/1535-stable-overflow-checks.md:43
msgid "Alternatives"
msgstr "替代方案"

#: src/1535-stable-overflow-checks.md:46
msgid ""
"The flag could instead be tied to crates such that any time code from that "
"crate is inlined/monomorphized it turns on overflow checks."
msgstr ""

#: src/1535-stable-overflow-checks.md:49
msgid ""
"We might also want a design that provides per-function control over overflow "
"checks."
msgstr ""

